This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a new automatic image annotation model. It also uses a generative adversarial network (GAN) model to train the proposed model, which is a popular technique in computer vision. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to generate diverse and distinct tags, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves text analysis and generation, which could place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image datasets, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
